# Dev Agency needs NO environment variables to run.
#
# A MASTER_KEY is auto-generated and persisted on the data volume on first boot; every credential
# and operational setting is configured in the dashboard (the onboarding wizard + Settings →
# Operations). The first visitor creates the admin account in-browser (/setup).
#
# Everything below is OPTIONAL — copy to .env and uncomment only to override a default.

# Pin the secrets-encryption key instead of the auto-generated one. Must stay STABLE — changing it
# makes all stored secrets undecryptable (run scripts/reset-master-key.mjs to wipe + start fresh).
# Generate: openssl rand -hex 32
# MASTER_KEY=

# Run mode: watch (default, polls GitHub) | webhook (event-driven, needs a public URL) | once
# RUN_MODE=watch

# Show a DEV badge in the UI (use on staging).
# AGENCY_ENV=development

# Seed the first admin headlessly instead of using the in-browser /setup screen.
# ADMIN_USERNAME=admin
# ADMIN_PASSWORD=
# ADMIN_EMAIL=

# Forgot the admin password? Set this, redeploy, log in, then REMOVE it again.
# RESET_ADMIN_PASSWORD=

# Webhook mode only — verify + auto-register GitHub webhooks.
# GITHUB_WEBHOOK_SECRET=

# SQLite location (default /app/data/agency.db in Docker; ./data/agency.db locally).
# DB_PATH=/app/data/agency.db
